{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-913f188543116075", "type": "tool_result", "content": "# NouveauVoice: Generating Novel Pseudo Speakers for Voice Anonymization\narXiv: 2607.03985\nAuthors: Meiying Melissa Chen, Anastasia Kuznetsova, Zhenyu Wang, Zhiyao Duan\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: \nStatus: unread\n===\n# MiniMax-Speech: Intrinsic Zero-Shot Text-to-Speech with a Learnable Speaker Encoder\narXiv: 2505.07916\nAuthors: Bowen Zhang, Congchao Guo, Geng Yang, Hang Yu, Haozhe Zhang, Heidi Lei, Jialong Mai, Junjie Yan, Kaiyue Yang, Mingqi Yang, Peikai Huang, Ruiyang Jin, Sitan Jiang, Weihua Cheng, Yawei Li, Yichen Xiao, Yiying Zhou, Yongmao Zhang, Yuan Lu, Yucen He\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We present MiniMax-Speech, a TTS model that supports 32 languages and generates high-fidelity speech, achieving SOTA results on multiple objective and subjective evaluation metrics.\n  2. Based on an autoregressive Transformer architecture equipped with a learnable speaker encoder, our model demonstrates strong expressiveness in zero-shot voice cloning and enhances speaker similarity in one-shot scenarios.\n  3. We employ a flow matching model based on our novel Flow-VAE, which further improves the audio quality and speaker similarity of the generated speech.\n  4. We detail several downstream applications of our model, including fine-grained control over emotional expression, extensive voice library via Text to Voice, and improving synthesis similarity by Professional Voice Clone.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/架构-AR-LLM, TTS/控制-参考语音, TTS/功能-多语言, TTS/功能-多说话人", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "f154d6d5-43c7-4ae8-9b50-952e770c6f4c", "uuid": "75d6bb07-385e-402f-9eb1-982309af09d6", "timestamp": "2026-07-20T09:34:14.745Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "# NouveauVoice: Generating Novel Pseudo Speakers for Voice Anonymization\narXiv: 2607.03985\nAuthors: Meiying Melissa Chen, Anastasia Kuznetsova, Zhenyu Wang, Zhiyao Duan\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: \nStatus: unread\n===\n# MiniMax-Speech: Intrinsic Zero-Shot Text-to-Speech with a Learnable Speaker Encoder\narXiv: 2505.07916\nAuthors: Bowen Zhang, Congchao Guo, Geng Yang, Hang Yu, Haozhe Zhang, Heidi Lei, Jialong Mai, Junjie Yan, Kaiyue Yang, Mingqi Yang, Peikai Huang, Ruiyang Jin, Sitan Jiang, Weihua Cheng, Yawei Li, Yichen Xiao, Yiying Zhou, Yongmao Zhang, Yuan Lu, Yucen He\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We present MiniMax-Speech, a TTS model that supports 32 languages and generates high-fidelity speech, achieving SOTA results on multiple objective and subjective evaluation metrics.\n  2. Based on an autoregressive Transformer architecture equipped with a learnable speaker encoder, our model demonstrates strong expressiveness in zero-shot voice cloning and enhances speaker similarity in one-shot scenarios.\n  3. We employ a flow matching model based on our novel Flow-VAE, which further improves the audio quality and speaker similarity of the generated speech.\n  4. We detail several downstream applications of our model, including fine-grained control over emotional expression, extensive voice library via Text to Voice, and improving synthesis similarity by Professional Voice Clone.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/架构-AR-LLM, TTS/控制-参考语音, TTS/功能-多语言, TTS/功能-多说话人", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
